<p style="text-align: justify;">Home Health Care Agencies are required by law to be licensed and bonded in order to conduct business. A surety bond establishes legitimacy for an agency and is required in order to prove that they are not engaging in fraudulent activity. Bonds ensure that any money owed to third party companies is paid properly and timely.</p>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: justify;">Home Health Care Agencies need to follow the necessary steps in order to apply for bonds. Bliss Marc will help you a) determine which surety bond is best for your agency and b) that you receive the best quotation. Other criteria required to apply for a bond:</p>
&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li>Complete application</li>
	<li>Undergo a credit check</li>
	<li>Submit financial statements</li>
	<li>Good financial standing</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<strong>ERISA BOND</strong>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA) regulates most types of employee benefit plans. A fidelity bond covers those responsible for managing the benefit plan. These bonds protect the participant and any beneficiaries from unjust fraud from anyone who handles the plan assets.</p>
&nbsp;

<strong>EMPLOYEE DISHONESTY BOND</strong>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Employee Dishonesty Bonds cover employers from losses as it pertains to dishonest or negligent action of their employees. Employers are reimbursed for employee losses such as theft, fraud and embezzlement of a company’s cash and/or assets. Employers are required to have Employee Dishonesty Bonds when one or more employees handle cash or company assets.</p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"]
