<h1>Fingerprinting</h1>
[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_separator color="#999999"][vc_column_text]<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Live Scan Fingerprinting</span></strong>[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_column_text]Bliss Marc provides the most convenient, fast and accurate live scan fingerprinting services. Whether you are required to be fingerprinted by a state and federal agency, or for employment, in minutes, our trained agents will ensure that your paperwork is in order, take your fingerprints, process the request and have you on your way!

&nbsp;

<em>What is Live Scan Fingerprinting?</em>

&nbsp;

Live scan fingerprinting is the process of capturing fingerprints electronically with our advanced live scan machine. With live scan fingerprinting, there is no ink or card. Your fingerprints are “rolled” across a glass plate and scanned. It is faster, cleaner, and more accurate than the old ink and roll method.

&nbsp;

A percentage of the population have hard to read fingerprints, which can be affected by age or exposure to work, such as construction or harsh cleaning or other chemicals. Our state-of-the-art equipment and highly trained staff, are able to maximize the quality of fingerprint images obtained, which reduces the likelihood of illegible fingerprints and will reduce the overall application processing time. The fingerprints are then submitted to the specific state or federal agency to process.[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_column_text]<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Fingerprint Card</span></strong>[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_column_text]At Bliss Marc, we value your time and your trust. We provide a comfortable environment with trained agents when you need a printed fingerprint card to take with you. This is an excellent item to store in your personal records – for you and your family members.

&nbsp;

<em>What is a Fingerprint Card?</em>

&nbsp;

Because many government organizations like the Department of Immigration and other federal agencies require physical copies of your fingerprints, Bliss Marc may offer the ability to digitally collect an applicant’s fingerprint images and then print them onto a standard fingerprint card (FD-258). Please note that fingerprint cards may not always be available. Make certain to check availability when scheduling your appointment.[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"]
