[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_separator color="#999999"][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_column_text]The State of Nevada now requires most health care companies to carry liability insurance as well as worker’s compensation! As of today, Nevada’ home health agencies, hospices and residential care facilities are all required to have valid worker’s compensation insurance and certain minimum limits of general and professional liability coverage.

&nbsp;

<strong>Businesses that fail to carry such insurance are having their licenses revoked. In addition, the Department is fining companies Hundreds of Thousands of Dollars for failure to carry worker’s compensation! The state is also cracking down on companies not carrying the required liability insurance and fining owners huge sums of money after closing them down!</strong>

&nbsp;

<strong>Worker’s Compensation</strong>

The State of Nevada can fine your company $15,000 for not having Worker’s Compensation and will hold you as the owner personally responsible for penalties and costs! Bliss Marc can help you avoid these massive fines and risks at a huge discount!
<a href="http://blissmarc.com/workers-compensation/">Click here to learn more&gt;</a>

&nbsp;

<strong>Liability Insurance
Home Health Agencies, Home Care Organizations, and Hospice</strong>

All HHAs, Skilled Nursing Services, and Hospices in Nevada must now have a general and professional liability insurance policy in the amount of at least one million dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence and three million dollars ($3,000,000) in the aggregate. We can save you money in meeting your Nevada insurance requirements and help you avoid being fined!
<a href="http://blissmarc.com/professional-general-liability/">Click here to learn more&gt;</a>

&nbsp;

<strong>AGCs</strong>

Nevada statutes mandate that all licensed AGCs, assisted living and residential care homes in Nevada must carry liability insurance and have surety bonds. The state requires you to prove your facility has general property damage, bodily injury, and professional (E&amp;amp;O) liability coverage of $1 Million per claim / $3 Million aggregate. You must also carry a surety bond of up to $50,000 (depending on number of employees)! This insurance can be so expensive that you have to close your doors, or, the state will fine you out of business for not carrying it. But Bliss Marc is here to help. We can beat the rates offered by other insurers and help you affordably meet state requirements.

<a href="http://blissmarc.com/rcfe-liability-insurance/">Click here for an instant quote&gt;</a>

